text.section:
Except as provided in a specific statute to the contrary, a criminal conspiracy is a:
Class C felony when the conspiratorial agreement is a violation of KRS 521.020 or 521.050;
Class B felony when the object of the conspiratorial agreement is a Class A felony or capital offense;
Class C felony when the object of the conspiratorial agreement is a Class B felony;
Class A misdemeanor when the object of the conspiratorial agreement is a Class C or D felony;
Class B misdemeanor when the object of the conspiratorial agreement is a misdemeanor.
